                        <h1>Teeth Whitening - Nutrition &amp; Fitness</h1>
                        <p>ED is caused by poor blood vessel function and is considered a sign you could be a candidate for heart disease. Enter: diet and exercise. The same things that help your heart could also help you not become impotent. Studies show a combination of diet and exercise can improve the risk of getting ED or impotence for millions of men.</p>
                        <p>In one study, a low-fat, low-cholesterol diet along with exercise resulted in about a third of the men with ED returning to healthy sexual functioning. In another study, men with a diet high in flavonoids had a 10 percent less risk of developing ED. Flavonoids are food compounds found in fruits, vegetables, and grains. Dietitians say the Mediterranean Diet is high in flavonoids.</p>
