                        <h2>Fitness</h2>
                        <p>No question exercise is good for you all around. &nbsp;But when it comes to your dental health, there are two things athletes do that can put your bright smile at risk.</p>
                        <p>One is heavy mouth breathing. It can dry out your mouth, and reduce the amount of saliva paving the way for bacteria to grow. The other is relying on sugary sport and energy drinks. Sure the electrolytes help hydrate you. But the excess sugar and acids can damage your teeth.</p>
                        <p>Water is a better alternative. One other suggestion? Drink the sports drinks with a straw.</p>
